		<part part_index="2" name="The Customs of Dragon Boat Festival" page="0" source="2">
      	<article allWordsNum="204">
            	<![CDATA[
Dragon Boat Festival is a traditional Chinese holiday. It is celebrated in memory of Qu Yuan.
Qu Yuan was a great poet of the State of Chu (楚国). He loved his country and gave much advice to the emperor. But the emperor didn't take his advice, and drove him out of the country. Qu Yuan was very sad, so he jumped into the Miluo River (汨罗河) on the fifth day of the fifth lunar month. Then the local people raced out in their boats to save him. This is said to be the origin of the festival.
During the festival, Chinese people usually race dragon boats and eat zongzi (粽子). Do you know that there are some other customs of the holiday?
<b><font color='#000000'>Hanging mugwort</font></b>
Hanging mugwort (艾蒿) is a custom that originated in the period of the Southern and Northern Dynasties (南北朝). Mugwort not only smells good, but also has the power to keep insects away and clean the air. This custom has been passed down from generation to generation.
<b><font color='#000000'>Carrying a spice bag</font></b>
It's believed that if you carry a small spice bag (香囊) around, it not only drives away evil spirits (恶魔), but also brings fortune and happiness to you. The small bags are usually hand-made by local craftsmen (工匠).
   	]]>
            </article>
